        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 27 at 7:33PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 733 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Byron, or 8 miles
northeast of Fort Valley, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, nickel sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Powerville and Byron.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
